</h2><p class="sc-hGMjVM kxdODp pf-63_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-213a6068-e0be-4df7-9e7e-87835d9226b9"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">Local authorities didn’t choose to innovate on a whim. Their evolving role as compliance enablers is a direct response to mounting pressures within the regulatory landscape. From increasingly complex standards to shrinking budgets and rising public scrutiny, councils are adapting not just to survive, but to lead. Below are the core drivers behind this transformation:
the world.<br>
</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-iLLNPL gTJAOY pf-66_"><strong>Regulatory complexity is rising</strong>
</h3><p class="sc-hGMjVM kxdODp pf-68_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-4c2d0b20-3be2-4645-9ff2-a1c2de112dda"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">With frameworks like CQC’s Single Assessment Framework and Ofsted’s focus on lived experience, local authorities must navigate overlapping standards across multiple sectors. Innovation becomes not just strategic, but essential.
